        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-10-29 08:02:32.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1\n> \n> (1 comment)\n> \n> > (1 comment)\n> \n> Actually, it worked, it just encoded \"=\" as \"\\u003d\"\n\nHi, Jim\nYes, It did work, but a checkstyle warning was reported that unicode should be avoided. How to suppress this warning in gerrit CI to make the CI build successful? Thanks!",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "a984618a10139054a9edffb3f8611ca1265e2a0c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-10-29 12:58:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> > Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1\n > >\n > > (1 comment)\n > >\n > > > (1 comment)\n > >\n > > Actually, it worked, it just encoded \"=\" as \"\\u003d\"\n > \n > Hi, Jim\n > Yes, It did work, but a checkstyle warning was reported that\n > unicode should be avoided. How to suppress this warning in gerrit\n > CI to make the CI build successful? Thanks!\n\nIt should work if you change \\\"=\\\" to \\\"\\\\\" + \"u003d\\\".\n\nThis does raise the issue that standard gson apparently converts a number of plain characters to unicode.  Should I modify the StandardCoder to disableHtmlEscaping, like had been done here?  I don't THINK any of our code embeds the json into html, but could be wrong.",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
      {
        "id": "96cc3033db5aafac4986395ec4f81b0b097b2835",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-10-29 13:24:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nAfter discussion with the team, we decided to modify the StandardCoder to disable html escaping.  Once that's done, this should work using \"=\".\n\nIn the meantime, you can wait until that's done, or you can change to use StandardCoder and change the \"=\" as mentioned in my previous reply.  I'll leave that up to you.",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
